name: "l'audace" zip up hooded sweatshirt (grey)
description: "il nous faut de l'audace, et encore de l'audace, et toujours de l'audace" translated into "We need audacity, and yet more audacity, and always audacity!" A saying that had become more of an aphorism during the french revolution. Articulated by Georges Jacques Danton, a pivotal figure in the french revolution, stated toward Charles William Ferdinand, Duke of Brunswick-Wolfenb√ºttel. Audacity is an insolent form of boldness, especially when imprudent or unconventional. It implies a degree of impudence, but also fearlessness and intrepid daring. Us being advocates of individuality and against conformity, It was only right to make art out of such an inspirational quote, completed with the signature of Georges Jacques Danton to give credit where credit is due. (produced in limited quantities)

name: "the rating" vintage inspired snapback (blue)
description: Inspired by the vintage caps of the 90's such as pro line, logo 7, or starter, and of course best to do it since, mitchell and ness. With a simplistic vintage feel, before puff embroidery or gaudy graphics became the trend. Showcasing our "the rating" logo, the cap features a high crown retro shape, flat embroidery, and bill based on original 'Brooklyn' style cap of the 1900's, with our signature "UN-united" tag near snap closure and green under bill with "Excelsior" artwork as an homage to the history of the original baseball cap. (Produced in limited quantities. Also available in black and blue)

And what do you get when harmony is disrupted? chaos, confusion, disorder, disorganization, disregard. Better known as the world in which we live. (Produced in limited quantities. Also available in white)
